[SN]TITLE[SN]
Blood poisoning warning to Dumfries and Galloway drug users

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
NHS Dumfries and Galloway has issued a warning to intravenous drug users after a number of cases of blood poisoning in the region.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
A spokesperson said it was in response to incidents over the last two months.
Posters carrying a warning message have been issued and NHS Dumfries and Galloway said it was working with the specialist drug and alcohol service to promote "safer injecting".
A meeting is also planned to "recommend any further measures as appropriate."
